	<p class="lead-italic">
		At Commonwealth Audiology, we want every patient to feel informed,
		supported, and confident when it comes to understanding their insurance
		benefits and payment options.
	</p>
	<p>
		Our goal is to make hearing care as accessible and stress-free as possible,
		and our team is here to guide you every step of the way.
	</p>

	<TableOfContents />

	<h2>Insurance Plans We Accept</h2>
	<p>We accept Medicare and all commercial insurance plans.</p>
	<p>Please note:</p>
	<ul>
		<li>We do not accept Medicaid.</li>
		<li>
			We do not participate with third-party hearing aid benefit programs such
			as TruHearing, NationsHearing, or similar plans.
		</li>
	</ul>
	<p>
		Many insurance plans offer partial or full hearing aid benefits; however,
		coverage varies widely. Hearing aid benefits cannot be guaranteed until
		your individual insurance plan is verified.
	</p>

	<h2>Insurance Verification</h2>
	<p>
		For all patients, with the exception of Medicare beneficiaries, we will
		verify benefits before your appointment so you have a clear understanding
		of what your plan may cover.
	</p>
	<p>
		If you are a Medicare patient, our team will review your Medicare
		guidelines with you and explain what services are included and those that
		are not.
	</p>

	<h2>Hearing Aid Coverage</h2>
	<p>
		Hearing aid coverage depends on the specific details of your insurance
		plan. While some plans may contribute toward hearing aids, others may not.
	</p>
	<p>
		When hearing aids are covered, the benefit amount, coverage frequency, and
		eligible devices will vary from plan to plan.
	</p>
	<p>Once your insurance is verified, we will explain:</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Whether you have a hearing aid benefit</li>
		<li>What portion of costs may be covered</li>
		<li>Whether deductibles or coinsurance apply</li>
		<li>What to expect financially during and after your fitting</li>
	</ul>
	<p>
		We make sure you have all the information you need before moving forward
		with treatment.
	</p>

	<h2>Payment Options</h2>
	<p>For your convenience, we accept:</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Credit cards</li>
		<li>Cash</li>
		<li>Checks</li>
	</ul>
	<p>
		We also partner with the Appalachian Assistive Technology Loan Fund,
		providing financing options for patients who prefer a payment plan.
	</p>

	<h2>Billing Process</h2>
	<p>
		Commonwealth Audiology will bill your insurance directly for covered
		services. Any remaining balances, including deductibles or coinsurance
		amounts, will be discussed with you before charges are applied.
	</p>

	<h2>Hearing Aid Trial Period &amp; Service Coverage</h2>
	<p>Your satisfaction is our priority. During your hearing aid trial period:</p>
	<ul>
		<li>All follow-up visits and related services are included.</li>
		<li>
			You will never be charged for adjustments, counseling, or appointments
			during this period.
		</li>
	</ul>
	<p>After the trial period ends:</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Follow-up visits and services are billed at standard rates.</li>
		<li>
			Repairs and part replacements covered under the manufacturer warranty are
			provided at no additional charge.
		</li>
	</ul>
	<p>
		We will always review your warranty details with you so you know exactly
		what is covered and for how long.
	</p>

	<h2>Here to Help You Feel Confident in Your Care</h2>
	<p>
		Navigating insurance and billing can feel overwhelming, but you don't have
		to figure it out alone. Our team is here to explain your benefits, answer
		your questions, and make sure you understand every step of the process.
	</p>
	<p>
		At Commonwealth Audiology, we're committed to delivering exceptional
		hearing care with honesty, clarity, and compassion.
	</p>
	<p>
		If you have questions about coverage or payment options, or if you'd like
		us to check your benefits, please <a href="/contact/">contact our office</a>.
	</p>
</InternalPage>
